  "content": "For VM/server deployment: `curl -fsSL https://apps.powerhouse.io/install | bash` installs Node 24, pnpm, and ph-cmd. Then `ph init <project>` and `ph service setup` runs an interactive wizard configuring: (1) Package installation (ph install custom packages); (2) Database (local PostgreSQL with auto-generated password, or remote connection URL); (3) SSL (Let's Encrypt for production with domain prompts, or self-signed for dev); (4) Domain setup (connect and switchboard subdomains). The script installs and configures Nginx with WebSocket support, security headers, and static file serving. PM2 handles auto-restart on crash and boot startup. Manage with `ph service start|stop|restart|status`.",
